# Commit message template for formazon.com
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <short summary>
#
# Types:
#   feat    - new feature or functionality
#   fix     - bug fix
#   docs    - documentation only
#   style   - formatting, no code logic changes
#   refactor- code changes that don't affect behavior
#   perf    - performance improvements
#   test    - adding or updating tests
#   build   - build system, dependencies
#   ci      - CI/CD configuration
#   chore   - maintenance, setup, configs, cleanup
#
# Common Scopes (optional but recommended):
#   (ui)      - shared components (Button, Tag, etc.)
#   (layout)  - global layout (Header, Footer, PageShell)
#   (home)    - home page specific
#   (work)    - work/portfolio pages and logic
#   (about)   - about page
#   (contact) - contact page and form
#   (content) - text content/data files (src/lib/content/*)
#   (config)  - tailwind, next.config, eslint, etc.
#
# Rules:
# - Use present tense, imperative mood: "add", "fix", "update"
# - Keep the first line under 70 characters
# - Do not end the first line with a period
# - One logical change per commit when possible
#
# Examples:
#   feat(home): add hero section
#   feat(work): implement "read next" case logic
#   refactor(ui): extract Button and TextLink components
#   style(about): fix mobile padding issues
#   chore(config): update tailwind theme tokens
#   fix(contact): resolve form submission error
#
# -------------------- COMMIT MESSAGE BELOW --------------------

<type>(<scope>): <short summary>

# Optional longer description:
# - Explain what and why, not how.
# - Add bullet points if needed.
#
# Optional references:
# - Closes #123
# - Related to #456